Description: Fender Stratocaster Neck (Mexico). Will be all maple for 6-string, right-handed strats. It’s straight, looks and plays well, nut is in good condition, original tuning machines but I replaced the string tree with a graphtech TUSQ tree. It has two small dents but that is the only issue. One dent is on the headstock (see pictures) and the other is on the back of the neck (see pictures) but you can’t feel it while playing. If you really want to trick out your guitar, I’d recommend getting the graphtech TUSQ nut to replace this one, and some auto-trimming, locking tuning machines like from Planet Waves. Then take it to a local luthier and have them set it up for your preference of action and string size (if you don’t know how to do that yourself). And then you will have a guitar that sounds and plays like a very expensive custom shop instrument.
